Acme Agent Supply Co. ("Acme," "we," "us") provides local-first operator tools. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect on acmeagentsupply.com (the "Site") and how we handle data you choose to share with us.
	1.	Local-first tools
Our Tools are designed to run in your environment. Unless explicitly documented otherwise, the Tools do not transmit your operational data to Acme.
	2.	Information we collect on the Site
We may collect limited information when you interact with the Site, such as:
• basic contact information you submit (for example, email if you choose to contact us)
• standard web logs from hosting providers (for example, IP address, user agent, and timestamps)
• cookies or similar technologies required for basic site functionality and security (if applicable)
	3.	Support bundles and operator data
If you choose to contact support, you may voluntarily send us a support bundle or other artifacts. We use that information only to help you troubleshoot and to improve reliability guidance. We do not access your environment unless you explicitly provide artifacts to us.
	4.	Sharing
We do not sell your personal information. We may share limited information with service providers that help us operate the Site (for example, hosting or email), only as needed to provide the service.
	5.	Data retention
We retain information only as long as needed for the purpose it was collected (for example, responding to a request, maintaining security, or complying with legal obligations).
	6.	Security
We use reasonable safeguards appropriate for a small, early-stage operation. No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.
	7.	Your choices
You can choose not to submit personal information through the Site. If you contact us, you can request deletion of the information you provided, subject to legal and operational constraints.
	8.	Changes
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last Updated" date controls.
